            { 738227793, "\"Alice was beginning to get very tired...of having nothing to do.\" How many times have I been in this place now? Was just trying to figure that out wh..." },
            { 738227794, "Ugh, this place is fucking miserable. And now I've gotta get chewed out by some asshole judge? Excuse me for not having more pep in my step. This cop ..." },
            { 738227795, "Things didn't exactly get any brighter once we got to the courtroom. Nobody here gives a shit, that's for sure. Not that I care. I just wanna be done ..." },
            { 738227796, "That judge may have had a point, but it's not like I can just change who I am. And if I get caught one more time, my life is over. Which is why I gott..." },
            { 738227797, "Lisa and her goons found me on my way home. Sounds like there was something important in that car they made me steal. How the fuck was I supposed to k..." },
            { 738227798, "Managed to give Lisa and her pals the slip. But it's freezing out here. Need to get home. Home to my empty-ass apartment and my stupid-ass cat. Okay, ..." },
            { 738227799, "Look at this palace—some thoughtful soul even made holes in the walls so the wind could let itself in. Alright, quick inventory... Favorite book...che..." },
            { 738227801, "One minute I'm fast asleep, the next I'm coughing my ass off and the place is burning down around me. Need to get the fuck out of here. But not withou..." },
            { 738227802, "No apartment. No money. No place left to go. My whole life up in smoke, just like that. I couldn't put Homer through any more of this. She'll be bette..." },
            { 738227803, "Back where it all began. Came into this world with nothing...and was about to leave that way too. But right when I'd said my last goodbye to Homer, I ..." },
            { 738227804, "I followed the glow, and it was coming from this bracelet sitting in an old abandoned store. Who leaves a thing like that in a place like this? Either..." },
            { 738227805, "What the fuck is going on? There was a weird-ass light, and next thing I know, I'm someplace I've never been before. And this bracelet thing won't fuc..." },
            { 738227806, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Very good of you to finally accept that I exist—although I will have to politely ask that you drop all that \"Cuff\" nonsense before ..." },
            { 738227807, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I expect you're suitably astonished to learn of my being no ordinary vambrace? Well, don't worry—I plan on sharing my considerable ..." },
            { 738227808, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Now do you understand why I was so \"freaked out\" by this \"fella\"? If you won't learn to listen to me, you'll be doing a lot more un..." },
            { 738227809, "<iconChapterSumVfx>It seems I've awoken some sort of dormant power within you. Lucky you. Now you just need to learn how to use it properly. Anyway, s..." },
            { 738227811, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Typical—we think we've finally found some friendly faces, and they brand you a monster and march us off at spearpoint! Seems whoeve..." },
            { 738227812, "<iconChapterSumVfx>So, here we are in Cipal. Rather unsporting of them to sentence you to death, I must say. Still, keep your powder dry for now. You ..." },
            { 738227821, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Charming. I go to all the trouble of waking you up, and you act as if I've done you a disservice! You do realize that lashing out a..." },
            { 738227822, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Well, that was entirely unexpected. But we're out—that's the main thing. And it seems I'm not the only one foolish enough to think ..." },
            { 738227824, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Thank goodness—the lower city at last. Rather different from Upper Cipal, isn't it? If what the peasant girl says is true, all thes..." },
            { 738227825, "<iconChapterSumVfx>\"Auden Keen,\" eh? And she helped you so you could help her help her homeland. That's about two \"helps\" too many, if you ask me. But..." },
            { 738227827, "<iconChapterSumVfx>So the peasant girl's father was researching these torana thingamajigs? Well, you never know—the answers you seek may lie in his wo..." },
            { 738227829, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Those clothes the peasant girl gave you really rather suit you, you know. Anyway, time to head out. You've read the map. I assume? ..." },
            { 738227830, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Just our luck to find the gate closed. I suppose they must be taking extra precautions after yesterday's escape. Even so, did you h..." },
            { 738227831, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Calling each other friends and handing over precious penlights? You've really taken a shine to young Olevia, haven't you? One can't..." },
            { 738227832, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Alright, it's off to the Cognoscents' Guild we go. Careful—Cipal is relatively safe, but we could be attacked at any time out here...." },
            { 738227833, "<iconChapterSumVfx>So this is the Guild. It's reasonably solidly constructed, but suffering somewhat from a case of neglect, I'd say. Not that that ch..." },
            { 738227834, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Well, we came in search of books, and we certainly found some. Working out which ones we're actually after is going to be something..." },
            { 738227836, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Who would have thought these books contained a secret that would further heighten your powers? Me, for one. You can thank me for my..." },
            { 738227837, "<iconChapterSumVfx>So not only have we found the journals, we've found the peasant girl's father, too. It never rains but it pours, eh? I must say, he..." },
            { 738227838, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Just our luck to find Sila's lackeys waiting for us downstairs. And here to arrest you for trespass, too. Very unfortunate. Well, t..." },
            { 738227839, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I must say, you're coming along handsomely. The Tantas' chosen are certainly not to be sniffed at, but you clobbered that lot handi..." },
            { 738227840, "<iconChapterSumVfx>It seems things are even worse than we thought. Sila's here. And she's looking for you. And she has Auden. AND the old man's run of..." },
            { 738227841, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Where can the old devil have got to? The peasant girl ran off after him too... Not that I expect we'll be getting much sense out of..." },
            { 738227842, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Alright, let's see what we can find out about Sila. Her underlings may be a handful, but they're nothing compared to the woman hers..." },
            { 738227843, "<iconChapterSumVfx>So the delightful Johedy used to work for Sila? I do wonder how much someone like that can be trusted... Still, she did give us the..." },
            { 738227844, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Are you all set? We've a hard road ahead of us, you know. I wouldn't leave town without being sure you've done everything you need ..." },
            { 738227846, "<iconChapterSumVfx>It's a long way to Sila's castle—and via some tough-looking terrain, too. I don't think the direct approach is going to be an optio..." },
            { 738227847, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Thank goodness. We managed to escape without another dragon fight. Let's try and never have one of those again, shall we? Now, onwa..." },
            { 738227848, "<iconChapterSumVfx>The Break is really quite ferocious here. I imagine it'll calm down eventually, but we shouldn't spend too long out in the open if ..." },
            { 738227849, "<iconChapterSumVfx>There's a cave nearby. We should be able to sit out the storm there. Which is lucky—I'm not sure how much more of this you can be e..." },
            { 738227850, "<iconChapterSumVfx>How lucky you are. The storm has finally subsided, and you have been blessed with a demonstration of my uncanny talent for mimicry...." },
            { 738227851, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Here at last. Not far to the castle now. But how to get in, exactly? Have you looked at the floor plan Johedy gave you? Maybe that ..." },
            { 738227852, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Well, we're inside the castle. I have to say it's something of a miracle we even made it this far. Sila will be in her throne room...." },
            { 738227853, "<iconChapterSumVfx>It's time to face Sila at last. Remember, this is the woman who attacked Cipal and killed your friend. Give this anything less than..." },
            { 738227854, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Good. We made it out of Sila's accursed city in one piece. Time to head back to Cipal for a well-deserved hero's welcome. Oh, and y..." },
            { 738227855, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Judging by the warm welcome, Auden must have been very worried about you indeed. And it seems word of your victory has spread alrea..." },
            { 738227856, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Well, if you wished to see how much your victory over Sila means to the people of Cipal, you need look no further than the happy fa..." },
            { 738227857, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Well, it didn't take long for the laughs to turn into screams. The Break from Avoalet has invaded the city. We should go and make s..." },
            { 738227858, "<iconChapterSumVfx>They may have been innocent citizens of Cipal until a moment ago, but no longer. And there's only one way to save those afflicted b..." },
            { 738227859, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I thought you'd sleep forever, you know. And please don't go collapsing like that again—I could really do without the excitement. T..." },
            { 738227861, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Olevia was well aware of how fleeting life can be. I suspect that's why she warmed to you so readily—she knew you might not be here..." },
            { 738227862, "<iconChapterSumVfx>So here we are in Avoalet. By all accounts, it was once a very beautiful place, but...well, those days are apparently over. No need..." },
            { 738227863, "<iconChapterSumVfx>That's hardly very sporting, is it? You come just as she asked, and they arrest you anyway. Tanta of Justice, indeed. Well, we're h..." },
            { 738227864, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Talk about going out with a bang—parting shots don't come much more explosive than \"By the way, Cinta's your mother.\" We'd better g..." },
            { 738227867, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Finishing Prav off earned you some shiny new powers, didn't it? You might be able to use them to make our journey home a little eas..." },
            { 738227868, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I know you're dead set on leaving, but did you really have to be so blunt with the poor girl? Perhaps taking a deep breath and tryi..." },
            { 738227869, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Johedy may think a visit to Junoon might be your best bet, but I have to say, I'm not so sure myself. After all, if Cinta's gone an..." },
            { 738227872, "I must have had some crazy dreams last night—I still feel super weird. But hey, Homer's in a good mood, which means I am too. Anyway, places to be. Be..." },
            { 738227873, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Thank goodness you finally heard me shouting at you to snap out of it! I thought you'd never cotton on! Anyway, Olas has woven toge..." },
            { 738227874, "<iconChapterSumVfx>So much for meeting the puppeteer herself—seems we'll have to make do with the puppet. Olas will do anything she can to keep you he..." },
            { 738227875, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Back in Athia at last. Never thought I'd be so happy to see the place. Looks like we're in Visoria—that's Olas's realm. I'm not sen..." },
            { 738227876, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Castles at the bottom of enormous holes, eh? Whatever will they think of next? Anyway, we need to find a way in. I'd imagine the pl..." },
            { 738227877, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Come on, Olas. You may have hoodwinked us with your illusions once, but we're hardly going to fall for the same trick twice. Let's ..." },
            { 738227878, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Good, inside the castle at last. I've never seen so many books, have you? I suppose she must take the \"Wisdom\" part of her title ve..." },
            { 738227879, "Holy shit. So Olas is dead and Cuff's transformed into some kind of demon!? I thought the Tantas were talking about me this whole time! I'm not about ..." },
            { 738227885, "I'm sorry, Homer...I had to stay and help. And it's lucky I did—that asshole's already attacked the town. I have to get everybody to safety while Cint..." },
            { 738227886, "Okay, everybody's safely in the archives. Now I just have to kill that backstabbing shitbag and end this once and for all. This might be my last chanc..." },
