            { 738228062, "\"A troop of soldiers were dispatched to a village in a far-flung corner of Praenost to further investigate the miasma. Certain of the villagers had co..." },
            { 738228063, "2/18/3878: Praenost's Refugees" },
            { 738228064, "\"The Praenostian forces retreated en masse to their fortresses, and were beset by citizens seeking refuge. Though they did not wish to abandon their c..." },
            { 738228065, "2/27/3878: The Long March from Praenost" },
            { 738228066, "\"The Corruption prevented Sila's orders from reaching the garrisons, and in the absence of their Tanta's leadership, confusion reigned among the ranks..." },
            { 738228067, "4/24/3878: Trouble in Praenost" },
            { 738228068, "\"While continuing our withdrawal to Cipal, we observed smoke rising from a nearby settlement. Commander Dax ordered the unit to investigate. Upon appr..." },
            { 738228069, "1/30/3878: Tyranny in Praenost" },
            { 738228070, "\"A rescue party dispatched from Cipal and led by Robian Keen happened upon a small village. The inhabitants were informed that the Corruption had spre..." },
            { 738228071, "3/29/3878: Slaughter in Praenost" },
            { 738228072, "\"Tanta Sila, having seemingly lost her mind entirely, ordered the borders closed, and dispatched her soldiers to villages across the realm, with order..." },
            { 738228073, "4/13/3878: Destruction in Praenost" },
            { 738228074, "\"A detachment of soldiers set out from Praenost to escort a group of elderly citizens and children to safety in Cipal. However, they were ambushed on ..." },
            { 738228075, "9/28/3877: Junoon Investigates the Break" },
            { 738228076, "\"It was decided that Cognoscents from each of the realms would be dispatched to investigate the strange mist-like phenomenon that had arisen. The aim ..." },
            { 738228077, "12/28/3877: The Break Spreads through Junoon" },
            { 738228078, "\"The fields of Junoon, whence such heady herbal scents had drifted for so many years, and in whose soil so many lifesaving medicines had grown... When..." },
            { 738228079, "9/25/3877: Junoon Debates the Break" },
            { 738228080, "\"When news first arrived of the blight afflicting the other realms, Robian Keen was quick to suggest that we do all in our power to aid the Cognoscent..." },
            { 738228081, "12/27/3877: Junoon Combats the Break" },
            { 738228082, "\"And we thought ourselves safe... Reports are pouring in of creatures afflicted by the Corruption having been sighted here in Junoon. And now we seek ..." },
            { 738228083, "8/1/3877: The Fall of Tanta Prav" },
            { 738228084, "\"Let the proceedings of the court be hereunder recorded. In the matter of the defendant accused of the theft of an apple, the verdict was one of guilt..." },
            { 738228085, "9/26/3877: The Fall of Avoalet" },
            { 738228086, "\"Several days after news first arrived of the strange affliction observed in Praenost, the same was reported in Avoalet. Guards were dispatched to inv..." },
            { 738228087, "2/29/3878: Avoalet's Refugees" },
            { 738228088, "A detailed diary, written to try and keep track of time in the dark of the cave in which the author was hiding. They seem to have fled from a village ..." },
            { 738228089, "2/10/3878: Avoalet's Misjudgment" },
            { 738228090, "\"We thought the law was meant to protect the innocent. But when Prav lost her mind, she used it to do the opposite. She passed laws forbidding us from..." },
            { 738228091, "2/17/3878: Avoalet's Misgovernment" },
            { 738228092, "\"Tanta Prav's sense of fairness was warped to the point where she was driven to insist upon the same misery for all, forcing those from areas not yet ..." },
            { 738228093, "3/3/3878: Avoalet's Betrayal" },
            { 738228094, "\"As if she had not done enough to terrorize her people, Prav's final act of depravity was to carry out what she euphemistically dubbed 'assisted conta..." },
            { 738228095, "9/17/3877: The Fall of Visoria" },
            { 738228096, "\"The Corruption continued to spill from the castle of Visoria, and in the city surrounding it, death and the disease the miasma brought with it held s..." },
            { 738228097, "9/26/3877: Visoria and Junoon" },
            { 738228098, "\"The Cognoscents of Visoria looked on, impassive and analytical, even as the Corruption claimed village after village. Many seemed to think it well wo..." },
            { 738228099, "7/30/3878: Visoria Bewitched" },
            { 738228100, "Despite having been lost to a Breakstorm, strangely, this village shows no signs of panic or disarray. A Nightmare appeared, and no one tried to escap..." },
            { 738228101, "4/13/3878: Visoria Besieged" },
            { 738228102, "The final testament of a man who watched his parents fall to the crazed creatures that attacked his village. He seems to have fled to safety after wit..." },
            { 738228103, "Phantom Minions" },
            { 738228104, "Compared to Sila and Prav, whose followers remain many and dedicated to this day, Olas has almost none. But she does have the power of illusion. And f..." },
            { 738228105, "1/23/3878: Boy's Diary: Day of Departure" },
            { 738228106, "\"Finally I get to set out with Robian's rescue party! We're going to go out there, and we're going to save people. Who knows—we might even save my mum..." },
            { 738228107, "1/26/3878: Boy's Diary: Robian's Persuasion" },
            { 738228108, "\"We found some survivors in a village in Praenost. They seemed to think they had no hope of escaping to safety, but Robian convinced them otherwise. W..." },
            { 738228109, "2/9/3878: Boy's Diary: The Corruption Spreads" },
            { 738228110, "\"We found some people in a village the Corruption was about to swallow. They were confused and terrified and screaming about how it was all over. But ..." },
            { 738228111, "2/22/3878: Boy's Diary: Ambushed" },
            { 738228112, "\"Robian shook me awake in the middle of the night and said we had to leave right away. I was still half asleep, and I didn't have a clue what was goin..." },
            { 738228113, "3/11/3878: Boy's Diary: The Journey Continues" },
            { 738228114, "\"We were near Cipal anyway, so we stopped in to get some supplies. Robian has a young daughter. I was sure he'd want to spend some time with her while..." },
            { 738228115, "6/17/3878: Boy's Diary: Familiar Ground" },
            { 738228116, "\"We got to Junoon, and we were just coming up to one of those fields of herbs they have there when Robian stopped and started staring off at the horiz..." },
            { 738228117, "6/30/3878: Boy's Diary: Discord" },
            { 738228118, "\"Robian said there couldn't be any survivors left in Junoon, and that we needed to head back to Cipal. Jennesh just said no. He said there were still ..." },
            { 738228119, "7/15/3878: Boy's Diary: The Long Road Home" },
            { 738228120, "\"We've been trying to find our way back to Cipal with the rest of the rescue party, but some got attacked by monsters, and others were swallowed by th..." },
            { 738228121, "7/31/3878: Boy's Diary: Wagon-Bound" },
            { 738228122, "\"Robian told me all kinds of stories. I just lay there on the cart and listened. I couldn't do much else—my leg's really badly wounded. We were attack..." },
            { 738228123, "8/13/3878: Boy's Diary: Memories" },
            { 738228124, "\"I knew deep down my mum and dad were dead. I've known it all along. So why am I even trying to get back to Cipal? What's the point? Robian's the one ..." },
