            { 738232274, "<iconChapterSumVfx>So this Pilo character wants to show you around? I've no idea if he's trustworthy, but he seems harmless enough. And who knows—you ..." },
            { 738232275, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Decided to take young Pilo up on his offer, did you? If nothing else, it'll be an opportunity to see if any of the townsfolk can be..." },
            { 738232276, "<iconChapterSumVfx>There certainly are a lot of desperate-looking people in the lower city, aren't there? I suppose resources are pretty scarce. Not s..." },
            { 738232277, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I quite liked their little pasture. Certainly a sight more relaxing than the lower city. And less crowded—didn't look like there wa..." },
            { 738232278, "<iconChapterSumVfx>So our perpetually addled friend Robian has lost something important, it seems. And...for reasons I can't begin to fathom, you're a..." },
            { 738232279, "<iconChapterSumVfx>For a man so clearly off his rocker, Robian certainly still commands his fair share of respect. Only to be expected if the tale of ..." },
            { 738232280, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Still no sign of whatever it was old Bob dropped, eh? But there's been no shortage of his admirers. \"Mentor,\" indeed. The mind bogg..." },
            { 738232281, "<iconChapterSumVfx>What do you think the chances are of the book that child gave us being what Robian was looking for? It certainly looks like it's se..." },
            { 738232282, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Johedy made Sila's armor, did she? And from the ore we found in Praenost, no less. Well, I'm certainly keen to see what she can mak..." },
            { 738232283, "<iconChapterSumVfx>This looks like the place Johedy marked on the map. And you did say we might as well look for her gear while we're here. There won'..." },
            { 738232284, "<iconChapterSumVfx>That's that beastly lot dealt with. Now we can get on with our search. Not that Johedy's given us the clearest of directions... Wel..." },
            { 738232285, "<iconChapterSumVfx>So the peasant girl finally worked herself to exhaustion. Hardly surprising if she's been slaving away over the wounded this whole ..." },
            { 738232286, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Goodness, Auden wasn't looking too chipper, was she? Still, what were you thinking, offering to help people in her place? Are you s..." },
            { 738232287, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Well, that's the sick and injured seen to. Your...unique style of patient care certainly didn't disappoint. Now we just need to fet..." },
            { 738232288, "<iconChapterSumVfx>That's the rations bagged. And I'm completely in agreement with Treahy about Auden's plight being entirely her own doing. But if yo..." },
            { 738232289, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Pilo wants to give you the grand tour again? Sounds like a total waste of time, if you ask me. But if you do insist on taking him u..." },
            { 738232290, "<iconChapterSumVfx>That little lot at the mausoleum were petrified of you until not so long ago, and now look at them—you'd think they couldn't live w..." },
            { 738232293, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Imagine that—the dreaded Johedy reading up on Cinta for your sake. For a woman who likes to tell you how little she's prepared to d..." },
            { 738232294, "<iconChapterSumVfx>A book chronicling the last days of Junoon and the sordid details of Tanta Cinta's pregnancy. And from the pen of our favorite disg..." },
            { 738232295, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Jennesh was certainly as charming as ever, if not more so. And he did know you were Cinta's daughter, after all. Sneaky devil. What..." },
            { 738232296, "<iconChapterSumVfx>That key of Jennesh's—he was one of Cinta's most faithful retainers, wasn't he? I'd imagine the castle might not be a bad place to ..." },
