            { 738233769, "Frey: Birth of a Legend" },
            { 738233770, "Tanta Cinta's beloved daughter.\n\nThe word \"Alfre\" is intricately embroidered on the blanket in which her mother wrapped her.\n\nCinta sent her infant ch..." },
            { 738233771, "Cuff: Trapped by the Tantas" },
            { 738233772, "A messenger once sent to Athia from another land.\n\nAccording to Cuff, the Tantas' infighting had already begun when he arrived. As a result, his attem..." },
            { 738233773, "Cuff: Frey's Best Bud" },
            { 738233774, "Frey's trusty traveling companion.\n\nWhile she likes to think of their partnership as a marriage of convenience, in truth, he might know her better tha..." },
            { 738233775, "Cuff: Frey's Right Hand" },
            { 738233776, "The tried-and-true companion who helped Frey break free from Olas's illusion.\n\nHe forced his way into the world the twisted Tanta had created, despera..." },
            { 738233777, "Sila: Tanta of Strength" },
            { 738233778, "A seasoned warrior, and the victor of countless battles.\n\nThough it was often said that none could rival her skill on the battlefield, she taught her ..." },
            { 738233779, "Prav: Tanta of Justice" },
            { 738233780, "Athia's irreproachable keeper of law and order.\n\nUnswervingly dedicated to the truth, Prav strove to better the people's lives so that all might prosp..." },
            { 738233781, "Cinta: Tanta of Love" },
            { 738233782, "A champion of the arts who passionately believed in freedom of expression and humanity's infinite potential.\n\nIn order to enrich the people's lives, s..." },
            { 738233783, "Auden: The People's Friend" },
            { 738233784, "A selfless young woman who puts herself on the line to aid others when the Break consumes Cipal.\n\nJust like her parents before her, she is prone to pr..." },
            { 738233785, "Auden: Solitary Beacon" },
            { 738233786, "A young woman who hides her own hardships from others.\n\nThe true motivation behind her altruism lies in the deaths of her parents. Unwilling to lose a..." },
            { 738233789, "Johedy: A Pact Honored" },
            { 738233790, "A former blacksmith who took up her tools again at Auden's request.\n\nAuden's earnest concern for her friend brought back Johedy's memories of a solemn..." },
            { 738233791, "Johedy: Down on Her Luck" },
            { 738233792, "A homeless woman who can often be found near Frey's apartment in \"New York.\"\n\nShe was fired from her job as a librarian when her boss discovered she w..." },
            { 738233797, "Dax: Still Loyal" },
            { 738233798, "Overseer of the city's security, including that of the mausoleum, where the townspeople go to pray for the departed.\n\nEven Sila is the subject of more..." },
            { 738233799, "Dax: Keeper of the Peace" },
            { 738233800, "A former general of Praenost who finally made her peace with Frey in the quiet before Cipal's greatest battle.\n\nThough she could not completely shake ..." },
            { 738233801, "Bellette: Regrets and Requests" },
            { 738233802, "The steadfast chairperson of the Council of Cipal. Having doubted Frey at first, she eventually came to see her as a potential force for good.\n\nThough..." },
            { 738233803, "Bellette: The Next Great Challenge" },
            { 738233804, "A wise councilperson of Cipal who was inspired by Frey to help bring back hope to her beloved city.\n\nHaving previously thought Frey Athia's only hope,..." },
            { 738233805, "Treahy: Think of Tomorrow" },
            { 738233806, "A dedicated educator disappointed by the children of Cipal's lack of interest in the pursuit of knowledge.\n\nFrey happened across Treahy just as he was..." },
            { 738233807, "Treahy: Fount of Wisdom" },
            { 738233808, "A Cognoscent of Visoria who worries deeply about Auden, daughter of his dear friend Robian.\n\nIn order to do what he can to help, he tells Frey about a..." },
            { 738233809, "Jennesh: Caged" },
            { 738233810, "A fanatical agitator against Frey who eventually lost his seat on the Council for his incendiary behavior.\n\nDespite having been imprisoned in the Towe..." },
            { 738233811, "Jennesh: Of Love and Hate" },
            { 738233812, "Despite sharing a homeland with Robian, this former citizen of Junoon was unmoved by his countryman's death.\n\nHis hatred for the much-missed Cognoscen..." },
            { 738233813, "Jennesh: The Fugitive" },
            { 738233814, "A wanted man who escaped from the Tower of Binnoi.\n\nAll that the former councilman left behind was a grisly message in blood. His guards assume that h..." },
            { 738233815, "Tavernkeeper: People's Publican" },
            { 738233816, "The proprietor of Cipal's one and only inn, who carries on business as usual despite the encroaching corruption.\n\nHe's keen to keep the tavern open, a..." },
            { 738233817, "Tavernkeeper: People's Champion" },
            { 738233818, "The landlord of the local pub, who insists on keeping the place going despite the pervasive air of despair.\n\nIt's his firm belief that hope is what ge..." },
            { 738233819, "Milia: Duty and Desire" },
            { 738233820, "A young woman born into a family who served as Sila's personal guard for generations.\n\nGiven her illustrious heritage, she was awarded the title of \"j..." },
            { 738233821, "Milia: Duty and Disappointment" },
            { 738233822, "A junior guard officer who was driven to despair at seeing so many of her friends and neighbors lost to the Break.\n\nWallace's ham-fisted attempt to pu..." },
            { 738233823, "Wallace: The Blue Bard" },
            { 738233824, "A bard who has taken to pondering life's ephemeral nature, and who is beginning to believe that nothing but tragedy awaits those who dare to love in s..." },
            { 738233825, "Wallace: What Worth's a Song?" },
            { 738233826, "A bard who is struggling to retain his faith in the healing power of music.\n\nWhen he attempted to convince a downcast Milia that there was no use in b..." },
            { 738233827, "A History of the Tantas" },
            { 738233828, "\"For as long as anyone can remember, our land has been ruled over by the Tantas, blessed be their names. It is not for us to know how their powers cam..." },
            { 738233829, "The Fall of the Tantas" },
            { 738233830, "\"Without warning, our former protectors became our oppressors. The difference in their conduct was stark and perplexing—they were aggressive, hateful...." },
            { 738233831, "The Corruption's Creep" },
            { 738233832, "\"As the Corruption continued to ravage our lands, robbing us of our food, our homes, and even our lives, we prayed for the Tantas to save us, as they ..." },
            { 738233833, "Pilgrims" },
            { 738233834, "Devotees once traveled from all over Athia to give thanks and offer up prayers at the temples raised in the Tantas' honor. No one knows quite when the..." },
            { 738233835, "Pilgrim's Refuges" },
            { 738233836, "These special shelters were built to provide safe resting places for the pilgrims who once traveled throughout the land visiting the various shrines a..." },
            { 738233837, "The Athian Script" },
            { 738233838, "The Athian alphabet was devised by the very first Tantas, who wished to promote literacy among their people. The plan was a success, and before the on..." },
            { 738233839, "The Depths of Corruption" },
            { 738233840, "The areas surrounding the Tantas' castles suffer from abnormally high concentrations of the Break. As such, any already Broken creatures that happen t..." },
            { 738233841, "Rusty Key" },
            { 738233842, "One of the keys needed to open the secret door that leads into Visoria Castle.\n\nWhile it may look perfectly ordinary, it has been enchanted by Tanta O..." },
            { 738233843, "Weathered Key" },
            { 738233844, "One of the keys needed to open the secret door that leads into Visoria Castle.\n\nThese keys were originally only meant for use in emergencies, and were..." },
            { 738233845, "The Rite of Remembrance" },
            { 738233846, "This ceremony was once held every year across Athia in order to commemorate the dead.\n\nTheir names would be written on lanterns that would then be rel..." },
            { 738233847, "Chapter 1: Attachments" },
            { 738233848, "Mere days before Christmas, Frey finds herself in court facing a charge of grand larceny. Luckily for her, Judge Maya Bird decides to give her one las..." },
            { 738233849, "Chapter 2: Stuck" },
            { 738233850, "The moment Frey picks up the bracelet, she finds herself transported to another world: Athia. And as if that weren't surprising enough, the bracelet t..." },
            { 738233851, "Chapter 3: The Interloper" },
            { 738233852, "With Auden's help, Frey manages to escape the Tower of Binnoi. The two women strike a deal—Frey will retrieve Auden's father's journals in exchange fo..." },
            { 738233853, "Chapter 4: What Must Be Done" },
            { 738233854, "Frey heads to the archives on Auden's recommendation to see if she can learn more about Sila. There, she meets Johedy, the archivist, who hands her a ..." },
            { 738233855, "Chapter 5: Might and Main" },
            { 738233856, "The morning after the Breakstorm, a bickering Frey and Cuff set out on the last leg of the journey to Praenost Castle. Finding a way inside isn't easy..." },
            { 738233857, "Chapter 6: Damned If You Do..." },
            { 738233858, "Despite having succeeded in avenging Olevia's death, Frey can't shake the sense that she's done something wrong. Nonetheless, she returns to Cipal to ..." },
            { 738233859, "Chapter 7: The Hue of Blue" },
            { 738233860, "Frey is tormented by horrific nightmares of the people around her becoming Broken. Unable to bear the burden of her guilt, she resolves to get home as..." },
            { 738233861, "Chapter 8: The Truth Will Out" },
            { 738233862, "In yet another courtroom—this time accused of Tantacide—Frey attempts to convince Prav that she was justified in killing Sila. Prav will not listen to..." },
            { 738233863, "Chapter 9: Breaking Point" },
            { 738233864, "Still reeling at the revelation that she might be Tanta Cinta's daughter, Frey rushes back to Cipal, desperate to save Robian and get some answers abo..." },
            { 738233865, "Chapter 10: None the Wiser" },
            { 738233866, "With emotions still running high after Robian's death, Frey and Auden get into a bitter quarrel about what Frey owes to Athia.\n\nDetermined to get some..." },
            { 738233867, "Chapter 11: Forspoken" },
            { 738233868, "Frey finally reaches the throne room of Visoria Castle, only to find Olas's body resting lifeless upon her throne.\n\nBefore she's even had a chance to ..." },
            { 738233869, "Chapter 12: Awakening" },
            { 738233870, "Frey and the dragon, who she now knows to be her mother, fly to the aid of Cipal. Though they put up a valiant fight, Susurrus fatally wounds Cinta, w..." },
            { 738233871, "Chapter 13: New Beginnings" },
            { 738233872, "Some time has passed since Frey's decisive battle with Susurrus, and while the Break has been driven from Cipal, most of Athia remains shrouded in cor..." },
            { 738233873, "The Archives" },
            { 738233874, "The archives are home to nearly every last scrap of knowledge remaining to the city of Cipal. The shelves are stocked with everything from old Cognosc..." },
            { 738233875, "Harkiska Grove" },
            { 738233876, "This land was once set aside for locals to cultivate their own produce. In the years since the Break arrived, however, it has been transformed into a ..." },
            { 738233877, "Cviceni Square" },
            { 738233878, "The square in Upper Cipal where the mausoleum is located. While it is much quieter than Obrana Square, it once played a central role in Athian culture..." },
            { 738233879, "The Council of Cipal" },
            { 738233880, "Officially known as the Council of Representatives, this interim governing body was created in order to manage Athia's affairs in the absence of the T..." },
            { 738233881, "Robian's Research" },
            { 738233882, "A journal containing Robian's research notes from his time at a Cognoscents' Guild in Visoria.\n\nHe appears to have devised a new method for delivering..." },
            { 738233883, "A Rare Celebration" },
            { 738233884, "When Frey returned to Cipal after killing Tanta Sila, she found the townspeople holding a party, elated by her triumph. To the long-beleaguered locals..." },
            { 738233885, "The People's Liberator" },
            { 738233886, "When Cipal was attacked by Susurrus, the townspeople were caught between the Break outside the city and the deadly monsters within. Frey kept her head..." },
            { 738233887, "Giril" },
            { 738233888, "A fragrant herb with a refreshingly sweet scent that grows in Avoalet. It is a highly prized medicinal ingredient.\n\nWhile Junoon is the realm most fam..." },
            { 738233889, "Smithing Tools" },
            { 738233890, "The tools of Johedy's old trade.\n\nWhile no one has used them in many a year, the metal still gleams underneath layers of dust. They are made from odva..." },
            { 738233891, "Jennesh's Diary" },
            { 738233892, "A journal that offers some insight into the events surrounding the fall of Junoon, as observed by Jennesh. It was once kept locked to maintain its aut..." },
            { 738233893, "Infusion of Giril" },
            { 738233894, "A potent medicine made by boiling down a mixture of dried giril and several other herbs. It has a strong soothing effect, and can increase one's focus..." },
            { 738233895, "A Tiny Key" },
            { 738233896, "A small, unadorned key given to Frey by Jennesh.\n\nShe doesn't know what it opens, but he clearly wanted her to have it for a reason." },
            { 738233897, "(Hold): Proceed" },
            { 738233898, "Not enough ingredients." },
            { 738233899, "You can't make any more of these." },
