            { 738235979, "<colorTextRed>You're nowhere near your destination.<colorEnd>\n(<buttonRestart>: Restart)" },
            { 738235982, "Dragon" },
            { 738236057, "<iconChapterSumVfx>An illusory enemy with no actual physical form. That shield is quite something. You won't be getting anywhere attacking from the fr..." },
            { 738236058, "<iconChapterSumVfx>An illusory enemy with no actual physical form. I probably don't need to remind you, but the wings are the weak point here. Go on—b..." },
            { 738236059, "<iconChapterSumVfx>An illusory enemy with no actual physical form. Eyes on those scales—that's how it telegraphs its moves. Oh, and don't give it time..." },
            { 738236060, "<iconChapterSumVfx>An illusory enemy with no actual physical form. If you can bring it to a standstill, it's not actually all that formidable. Why not..." },
            { 738236061, "<iconChapterSumVfx>An illusory enemy with no actual physical form. These poor wretches don't even have the benefit of once having been human. Just put..." },
            { 738236062, "<iconChapterSumVfx>An illusory enemy with no actual physical form. Even the fake ones can still heal themselves, though. Perhaps a little poison might..." },
            { 738236063, "<iconChapterSumVfx>An illusory enemy with no actual physical form. Poison really is the pits, isn't it? Trap it in place and clobber it until it falls..." },
            { 738236064, "<iconChapterSumVfx>An illusory enemy with no actual physical form. They're cunning little so-and-sos, but keep your distance, and you should be fine. ..." },
            { 738236065, "<iconChapterSumVfx>An illusory enemy with no actual physical form. But though it may be a mirage, its voice is very real indeed. Finish it off before ..." },
            { 738236066, "<iconChapterSumVfx>An illusory enemy with no actual physical form. These filthy creatures like to fling their gastric juices about the place—an experi..." },
            { 738236067, "<iconChapterSumVfx>A huge lamp that can call forth illusory enemies, and which features an in-built defensive shield. Mop up the riff-raff, then smash..." },
            { 738236068, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Some sort of illusion-generating device. If you don't deal with it, it will just keep pumping out enemies, so prioritize putting it..." },
            { 738236069, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Some sort of illusion-generating device. You'll have to deal with the enemies it summons before it will let down its defensive shie..." },
            { 738236070, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Seems the place is crawling with these feral menaces. They rely on being swift on their feet, so you might want to try and find a w..." },
            { 738236071, "<iconChapterSumVfx>They may not be much to worry about on their own, but a pack of them is an altogether different proposition. Oh, and they're absolu..." },
            { 738236072, "<iconChapterSumVfx>You have to admire the commitment to the whole \"insane wild dog\" aesthetic. And that tail looks like it would hurt... I'd stay back..." },
            { 738236073, "<iconChapterSumVfx>It really is unnerving what the Break can conjure up, isn't it? And does it have to move quite so...disturbingly? Whatever you do, ..." },
            { 738236074, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Get your notebooks out, creature spotters—this is a rare one! A rare one with a precious treasure to share, no less. You'll need to..." },
            { 738236075, "<iconChapterSumVfx>You like cats, don't you? Well, this one's both wily and wary. Don't charge in thoughtlessly. Stop it in its tracks first." },
            { 738236076, "<iconChapterSumVfx>And here I was thinking these things couldn't get any more...baroque. This one looks like it's waiting for an opportunity to hit ba..." },
            { 738236077, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Hmm. Has a certain regal air, doesn't it? My advice would be to try and take it out before it can get really angry. If you can't ma..." },
            { 738236078, "<iconChapterSumVfx>It may have taken on a slightly more intimidating form, but in the end, this one's still more hunted than hunter. Not that those an..." },
            { 738236079, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Gosh. The Break's turned this one into quite the muscle-bound monster, eh? If it leaps into the air, watch out for the ensuing shoc..." },
            { 738236080, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Is it me, or have the antlers on this one gone completely bonkers? I'd definitely try to avoid standing directly in front of it if ..." },
            { 738236081, "<iconChapterSumVfx>It's quite beautiful, isn't it? But don't get too distracted by its handsome weapon of a head—if it trots off into the air, you're ..." },
            { 738236082, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I do so love a rare breed. This one will try to escape to high ground, but I'd say you're more than nimble enough to follow." },
            { 738236083, "<iconChapterSumVfx>These things look relatively docile, but looks can be deceiving. They're rather given to fits of violent rage. Dodging its charges ..." },
            { 738236084, "<iconChapterSumVfx>This one's certainly quite far along in the old mutation stakes. I wouldn't go any closer to its horns than you absolutely have to...." },
            { 738236085, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Horn assessment: hopelessly, fatally Break-warped. If you're looking to wear it down with counters, you'll need to proceed with ext..." },
            { 738236086, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Goodness. I hope for your sake it's not as deadly as it looks—even I have my limits, you know. Try and knock it on its back so I do..." },
            { 738236087, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Are those its bones I can see? Ugh, the Break really does do some disgusting things. Anyway, charge in without thinking here, and y..." },
            { 738236088, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I wouldn't think you could absorb much more of the Break than this abomination has. Anyway, the main things to remember here: watch..." },
            { 738236089, "<iconChapterSumVfx>It's sort of a pared-down artistic rendering of a bear, isn't it? But while it may look insubstantial, I'd advise you not to get on..." },
            { 738236090, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Well, the rare ones are usually pretty flighty, but in this instance, I think we're dealing with something a little different. I mi..." },
            { 738236091, "<iconChapterSumVfx>You do have a habit of sniffing out the most terrifying creatures in all creation, don't you? And to make matters worse, you won't ..." },
            { 738236092, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Aww, isn't it just the cutest? No. No it isn't. I'm rather a traditionalist when it comes to mouths, and this thing has one...on it..." },
            { 738236093, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Is there such a thing as being made of mouths? Well, if there wasn't, there is now. These creatures have a nasty habit of surprisin..." },
            { 738236094, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Did someone say \"more fangs than one could shake a stick at\"? It wouldn't do anything so awful as...fire them at you, would it? Bes..." },
            { 738236095, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I don't think you need me to tell you that this one's pretty thick-skinned. So you'll need to get up close rather than chipping awa..." },
            { 738236096, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Something tells me this one won't be easy to catch unawares. If you're going in close, you'll need to watch its tail—and its mouth,..." },
            { 738236097, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I thought it looked like some sort of...walking fish from a distance. But no. It's altogether worse. Whatever you do, don't try fig..." },
            { 738236098, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I have a very bad feeling about this one. If it dives beneath the ground, be very, very careful indeed. And when it is visible, don..." },
            { 738236099, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Look! A rare breed! And it's carrying some sort of treasure. I think these have a tendency to make underground escapes, though. Hit..." },
            { 738236100, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Please don't tell me you're actually going to try and fight this thing? Going in the water with it would be suicide. As would getti..." },
            { 738236101, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Awful little creatures, these. Given to scuttling about the place being generally unsettling. Those fangs and teeth look poisonous,..." },
            { 738236102, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Well, I'd say the Break has worked its awful magic pretty thoroughly on this one. The poisonous mist it emits is a thoroughly unple..." },
            { 738236103, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Extended exposure to the Break seems to have turned this one's entire insides to poison. And anywhere that poison spills will be co..." },
            { 738236104, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Hmm... Yes, far from formidable, I'd say. You'd be wasting your time attacking each one individually, so choose an attack with a wi..." },
            { 738236105, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Birds are usually quite intelligent creatures, but this one's lost its tiny mind. Try to hit it out of the air when it swoops in fo..." },
            { 738236106, "<iconChapterSumVfx>White feathers, eh? Showy little blighter. It seems to be some kind of scout. Get rid of it quickly before it can call for backup." },
            { 738236107, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Is it a bird? Is it a ball? Whatever it is, it's building up to something. I'd say you might want to stop it before it can finish t..." },
            { 738236108, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Ooh, it's a rare one. Which means we should definitely try to take it down. Quickly, before it disappears!" },
            { 738236109, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Ooh, big chap. You won't walk away from this one unscathed, but something tells me you're going to charge in anyway. If you do insi..." },
            { 738236110, "<iconChapterSumVfx>The carrion-eating picker-clean of the plains. And a diet of rotten filth really does turn one's guts toxic—try not to let it belch..." },
            { 738236111, "<iconChapterSumVfx>These things are a pain when they're up in the air, but they quite often float down to the ground for a breather. I'd just wait unt..." },
            { 738236112, "<iconChapterSumVfx>As if the Break couldn't make things any worse, it's gone and turned this one's guts even more rancid. Knock it out of the air befo..." },
            { 738236113, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Humans who get caught up in the Break end up in this pitiful state. There's no saving them—just put them out of their misery." },
            { 738236114, "<iconChapterSumVfx>This one may look vaguely human, but it's a surface similarity and nothing more. It's not exactly wily when it comes to defending i..." },
            { 738236115, "<iconChapterSumVfx>The rare ones are usually pretty swift on their feet, but this one's an absolute shambles. Which should make it easy enough to chas..." },
            { 738236116, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Do you think this thing was human once? If it was, it's put on some serious muscle since then. Gosh—and learned how to heal itself...." },
            { 738236117, "<iconChapterSumVfx>They don't come much more physically formidable than this. Not recommended unless you're feeling supremely confident. If you're goi..." },
            { 738236118, "<iconChapterSumVfx>And how exactly is one supposed to take on something like that? Its defenses are essentially impenetrable, and if it hits you even ..." },
            { 738236119, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Quite the nifty mover, isn't it? I think you might want to watch out for its breath as well. Maybe trapping it in place and wallopi..." },
            { 738236120, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Goodness. \"Say it with spikes\" is the motto here, I'd imagine. Which is a shame, as the best approach would seem to be to go in clo..." },
            { 738236121, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Fast, flighty, and itching to stab you in the back the first chance it gets. Riddle it with holes from a distance—and don't let it ..." },
            { 738236122, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Small in this case does not mean easy to deal with. A well-organized gang of these insufferable creatures can be deadly. I'd recomm..." },
            { 738236123, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I've seen the Break do a lot of things, but giving people wings—that's a first. Anyway, you've got your work cut out here. An airbo..." },
            { 738236124, "<iconChapterSumVfx>With wings like that, it can move in ways its human incarnation could never have dreamed of. If it comes close, clobber it before i..." },
            { 738236125, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Hmm. Unsettling eye-based life-forms are never good news, I'm afraid. I'd keep moving, and stay out of its line of sight—that is no..." },
            { 738236126, "<iconChapterSumVfx>This one's blessed with powers of perception that almost beggar belief. Once it spots you, there'll be nowhere to hide. Oh, and if ..." },
            { 738236127, "<iconChapterSumVfx>The power it holds in those hands is like nothing else you'll have seen. You need to destroy it before it unleashes...whatever it's..." },
            { 738236128, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Well, good luck predicting the movements of all those tentacles. Or damaging the abominable creature with most of your attacks, for..." },
            { 738236129, "<iconChapterSumVfx>One of Sila's underlings. I doubt your magic will put so much as a scratch in that shield. You might be better off trying to find a..." },
            { 738236130, "<iconChapterSumVfx>One of Prav's pet hunters, eh? Well, they're quick enough on their feet and fond enough of firing off endless streams of arrows tha..." },
            { 738236131, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Another one of Sila's servants. It may be big, but it can flap about the place at a fair old speed. I'd focus on clipping its wings..." },
            { 738236132, "<iconChapterSumVfx>These are the faithful servants through which Prav likes to administer her own unique brand of justice. The axes they carry are wor..." },
            { 738236133, "<iconChapterSumVfx>It seems it's keeping Olas's illusions alive somehow... But never mind that—it's going to throw some extremely disorienting tricks ..." },
            { 738236148, "<iconChapterSumVfx>I think this monstrosity might be why everything around here looks a little worse for wear. Attacking from a distance would probabl..." },
            { 738236149, "<iconChapterSumVfx>The Tanta of Strength herself, eh? Well, she may have lost her mind, but she's every bit as dangerous as she ever was. If you get t..." },
            { 738236150, "<iconChapterSumVfx>At last we face the Tanta of Justice herself. Her ability to manipulate gravity is rather troublesome, but at least you've got me t..." },
            { 738236154, "<iconChapterSumVfx>Your journey ends here, Frey. Neither you nor anyone else will stop me from wreaking my revenge. You will be annihilated—you and yo..." },
            { 738236155, "<iconChapterSumVfx>How exactly do you think you'll be able to defeat me, Frey? Surely there is a limit even to your foolishness? Well, I shan't make y..." },
