            { 738244143, "Thalia: Marked with Magic" },
            { 738244144, "Frey discovers that Thalia is now capable of magic—a likely side effect of the strange mark left by General Aldacor. While Thalia's magic feels unfami..." },
            { 738244145, "Thalia: Unwitting Weapon" },
            { 738244146, "As Frey destroyed the roots of the Tree of Offering, her magical power continued to grow, and the tattoo-like markings that covered Thalia's right arm..." },
            { 738244147, "Thalia Solarius" },
            { 738244148, "A young woman who lost her life during a mysterious Rheddig rite known as the Gloaming.\n\nThalia was a onetime member of Tanta Olas's personal guard wh..." },
            { 738244149, "Tanta Cinta: Fire of Youth" },
            { 738244150, "The Tanta of Love and ruler of Junoon as she was twenty-five years ago, in the time of the Rheddig invasion. Frey was somewhat surprised to learn that..." },
            { 738244153, "Cinta: A Decision Made" },
            { 738244154, "The Tanta of Love and liberator of Visoria.\n\nThough she initially infiltrated Visoria Castle to assassinate the unwitting weapon, Thalia Solarius, she..." },
            { 738244155, "Gilotis Aldacor" },
            { 738244156, "The general who led the Rheddig invasion of Visoria and left a mysterious mark on Thalia's arm. A cruel and calculating leader, he is more than willin..." },
            { 738244157, "Gilotis Aldacor" },
            { 738244158, "A Rheddig general whose dedication to his duty was so total that he did not hesitate to transform himself into a slavering beast when the need arose. ..." },
            { 738244159, "Susurrus: Seeds of Destruction" },
            { 738244160, "A single golden bird was given flight by Thalia's final sacrifice—a creature so tiny and insignificant it could hardly be described as evil. But in ti..." },
            { 738244161, "A member of the force sent from Rheddah to invade Athia, equipped with a weapon imbued with the power of a certain magical ore. Specializes in mid-ran..." },
            { 738244162, "A member of the force sent from Rheddah to invade Athia. Specializes in mid-range spear attacks, and while not hugely fast, benefits from a sturdy shi..." },
            { 738244163, "A member of the force sent from Rheddah to invade Athia, equipped with a bow imbued with the power of certain magical ores. These agile archers prefer..." },
            { 738244165, "The Rheddig army relies on magical ore as the source of its formidable power, and this member of the Rheddig force has gone as far as to incorporate i..." },
            { 738244177, "Olas's Personal Guard" },
            { 738244178, "It was important to Tanta Olas that her personal guard be composed of soldiers who possessed both brains and brawn. Naturally, this was a lot to ask, ..." },
            { 738244187, "The Old Capital of Visoria" },
            { 738244188, "A subterranean town as old as Visoria Castle itself. As the years went by and the town's population grew, it could no longer support the needs of its ..." },
            { 738244189, "Talismans" },
            { 738244190, "Special insignia worn by members of Olas's personal guard. Each one has been blessed by the Tantas themselves, granting its wearer a beneficial effect..." },
            { 738244205, "Rheddah" },
            { 738244206, "A land just across the sea from Athia, from which the Rheddig hail. There is a long history of combative encounters between the two nations, but the i..." },
            { 738244209, "The Purge of the Rheddig" },
            { 738244210, "When the Rheddig invaded twenty-five years ago in the days leading up to what would come to be known as the Purge, to say that they caught the Athians..." },
            { 738244223, "The Mark" },
            { 738244224, "The strange mark that General Aldacor left on Thalia's arm, and evidence that Thalia had been transformed into a vessel. While it did grant Thalia mag..." },
            { 738244227, "The Tree of Offering" },
            { 738244228, "A magical tree perched atop Visoria Castle, whose tremendous growth was a result of the many \"offerings\" made to it in the form of human lives. Its ro..." },
            { 738244231, "The Gloaming" },
            { 738244232, "A ceremony at sunset by means of which one marked as a vessel will fully complete their transformation. Aldacor's first attempt to perform this in Ath..." },
            { 738244233, "The Truth behind the Gloaming" },
            { 738244234, "The true purpose of the Gloaming was to resurrect the Rheddig's ultimate weapon, the ancient demon Susurrus. To do this, the Rheddig needed to infuse ..." },
            { 738244247, "A traditional concoction made of balm flax that's capable of curing all manner of ailments. There's hardly an Athian out there who doesn't know how to..." },
            { 738244268, "Trader" },
